<p>The <code>tidy</code> tag formats and beautifies HTML content.</p>

<h2>Basic Tidy</h2>
<pre>{open}tidy{close}
&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Messy&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;HTML&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
{open}/tidy{close}</pre>
<p>Result (formatted):</p>
<pre>{tidy}<div><p>Messy</p><span>HTML</span></div>{/tidy}</pre>

<h2>Nested HTML</h2>
<pre>{open}tidy{close}
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;One&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Two&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Three&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
{open}/tidy{close}</pre>
<p>Result:</p>
<pre>{tidy}<ul><li>One</li><li>Two</li><li>Three</li></ul>{/tidy}</pre>

<h2>Table Formatting</h2>
<pre>{open}tidy{close}
&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Name&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Value&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;A&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
{open}/tidy{close}</pre>
<p>Result:</p>
<pre>{tidy}<table><tr><th>Name</th><th>Value</th></tr><tr><td>A</td><td>1</td></tr></table>{/tidy}</pre>

<h2>Use Case</h2>
<p>The tidy tag is useful for:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Debugging - see the actual HTML structure</li>
  <li>Code generation - create properly formatted output</li>
  <li>Export - clean HTML for external use</li>
</ul>
